.TH VV-INIT 1 "2026-02-27" "vv v0.3.0-1-gcde4c06-dirty" "Vibe-Vault Manual"
.SH NAME
vv-init \- create a new Obsidian vault for session notes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vv init [path] [\-\-git]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a fully configured Obsidian vault with Dataview dashboards,
Templater templates, and session capture infrastructure. Also writes
a default config to ~/.config/vibe\-vault/config.toml pointing at the
new vault.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B path
Target directory (default: ./vibe\-vault)
.TP
.B \-\-git
Initialize a git repository in the new vault
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
vv init                       Create ./vibe\-vault
vv init ~/obsidian/my\-vault   Create at a specific path
vv init \-\-git                 Create with git repo initialized
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vv (1),
.BR vv\-hook (1),
.BR vv\-check (1)
